{"_id":"aKovTMbPzfmUU53V","name":"World Traveler","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This character is familiar with other nations and cultures, and  ignores the Outsider penalty when dealing with locals (see Setting Rules, Outsiders, in the Rippers Resurrected Player’s Guide).</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 19","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 19","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dygc9en5q1d","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"bJqdsU5FOjwSMXkl","name":"Need For Speed","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot knows how to push their craft beyond design specs; they may add 1/2 Speed on a Success or double speed on a Raise for the next round.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d8, Ace Edge"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_us2p9cunc3","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"bYBsQBHjWdfMGunZ","name":"Visions","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Dark dreams or flashing visions of doom and dread fill this person’s thoughts. While they are disturbing, they are often useful as well.</p><p> Once per game session, the visionary is granted a vision. This may be a sudden flash that can occur at any time, a nightmare that only happens when sleeping, or it may be an active process such as reading tea leaves or tarot cards. When this occurs, use the Signs & Portents system described on page 28.</p><p> Immediately after, the visionary must make a Smarts roll. If the roll is failed, the visions take their toll on her mind, confusing fantasy with reality, the past with the present, or simply straining the mind with arcane energy. The seer loses 1 Sanity point.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 7","notes":"Horror Companion, page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3bzlxtfggr2","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"cFSzUUCszCTe2rVB","name":"Techie Tinker","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot is more than cable of altering and hack-rigging their vessel. The Pilot increases Handling, Toughness, or Armor by +1. This Edge may be taken once per Rank.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d6, Repair d6, Electronics d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_us2p9cunc3","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"cbtCA1cqPEpkiuXo","name":"All The Senors","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot uses caution and craft positioning to produce the best sensor results. Add Handling to Notice Trait rolls with craft scanners.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d6, Electronics d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_us2p9cunc3","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"e36sNzI2yZZyZaen","name":"Arcane Chemist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Ripping and distilling extracts from monsters is something of a specialty for this hero. When making extracts, a Ripper with this Edge creates twice as many doses as usual.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 17","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Science d6,  Rippertech d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dygc9en5q1d","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"exPlVBRxvaaxujLO","name":"One Shot Left","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character will always have at least one projectile remaining for his or her ranged weapon, even after an extended combat. This might be a final bullet in a gun, arrow in a quiver, or stone in a sling. This option does not remove the need to reload weapons in a game that uses realistic ammunition rules, but rather assures that the character will not be forced to reload at a critical moment.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 79","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 79","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Shooting d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1zofuj1e709","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"flWGD5THfR2ENI3M","name":"Tomb Fighter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Those who battle dead things in tight spaces have learned special techniques to take advantage of their confines. Frazer’s Fighters are famous among the Rippers for their battles Egypt’s crypts and tombs, but any close quarters combatant may take this Edge.<p>The hero gains +1 to Parry for each wall within 1” (2 yards) of his position, up to a maximum of +3 if his back is against a dead end or cul-de-sac.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 18","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Fighting d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dygc9en5q1d","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"flptzw40C1bF5gG8","name":"Paragon","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The greatest Rippers are righteous individuals and fierce protectors of the innocent. They lead by their austere example and are willing to aid any who fight the dark powers of the Cabal.<p>When this character gives a Benny to another who uses it to make a Trait roll (including Soak rolls), the recipient adds +2 to the final total. This stacks with Elan if the beneficiary has the Edge.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 18","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Common Bond"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dygc9en5q1d","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"hnBUccEqWG8Y7rPJ","name":"Grim Fatalism","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Old Worlders come from a grim, superstitious, and fatalistic land. Even children know most of the legends concerning vampires and werewolves— add +2 to Knowledge (Occult) rolls concerning such creatures.<p>More importantly, Old Worlders’ fatalism steels their mind against the abominations that stalk the tall crags and dark forests of their homes. When an Old Worlder with this Edge is Panicked or Paralyzed by fear (see the Fright Table on page 31), he ignores any movement limitations or requirements. He treats both results simply as Shaken instead.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 17","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Old Worlders)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dygc9en5q1d","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"ioPbVsURG5LjY4SZ","name":"Gone Native","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When immersed in a foreign culture for long periods, Rippers invariably adopt some of the habits and customs of their hosts.<p>Frazer’s Fighters are particularly known for the affectations they adopt after living in and around Egypt and the Middle East for years on end. While these traits don’t endear them to polite London society, they help the Fighters blend and integrate with the native populace more easily, and withstand the native climate better than other foreigners.<p>Characters who have Gone Native are acclimated to the local environment, ignoring one point of penalties when resisting <i>natural</i> Fatigue from environmental effects. The character also gains + 2 Persuasion with the locals but is still considered an Outsider (unless she also has World Traveler).</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 17","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dygc9en5q1d","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"kARGTEGbUa8Uya9L","name":"Down-to-Earth","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero is of sound mind and not prone to flights of fancy. Although the supernatural is still frightening, he or she has the good sense to remain rooted in reality. A character with this Edge is more likely to be able to deal with the many horrors of the Cabal and can better resist rippertech’s harmful effects. Modify this hero’s Reason by +1.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sp d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dygc9en5q1d","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"kxEGCJzjunzUVOQC","name":"Master of Disguise","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This charlatan is capable of disguising himself as a completely different person and acting as if a member of any other social class.<p>Creating a disguise normally takes 15 minutes and a disguise/makeup kit. Disguising one’s self as a higher social class also requires the appropriate clothing (lower class clothing might be faked by disheveling better clothes).<p>A disguise may be created without a kit at a –2 penalty, and it may be done more quickly (1d6 rounds) by taking a –2 penalty as well (these may be combined to do a fast disguise with no kit at –4). Those who know the character in his other guise may make an opposed Notice roll as detailed under Alternate Identity.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 19","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 19","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Alternate Identity, Performance d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dygc9en5q1d","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"lBz1x2B7djCS4gsW","name":"Mystic Pact","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Though the Rosicrucians are dispersed at this time in the world of Rippers, a few individuals remain and continue to espouse the cause.<p>When the order was active, new recruits were often taught mystical symbols and practices that enhanced their magical abilities.<p></p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 17","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Rosicrucians)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dygc9en5q1d","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"lhBjTB5tYmPTmE1W","name":"Charms & Wards","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Witch hunters spend their days tracking down witches, hags, and rogue priests, and know how to prepare certain minor charms, tattoos, symbols, and even odors or ointments to ward off their evil eyes.<p>Black magic (and Special Abilities that mimic such power) used against the hero suffers a –2 penalty to the arcane skill roll.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Witch Hunter)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dygc9en5q1d","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"lw4h4qJRQZ5lPK1X","name":"Relentless","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your slayer is truly driven to defeat evil. He must seek it out wherever he suspects it lies, and brooks no interference from those he thinks bar his way.</p><p> In exchange for this dogged determination and unflinching dedication to the chase, Relentless characters who get a success to recover from being Shaken may take a single action.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 5","notes":"Horror Companion, page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3bzlxtfggr2","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"n1qGe0hbv0RqkeGT","name":"Vanishing Act","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The art of using moving objects, people or vehicles, as cover to make good a getaway. This operative is practiced in crossing the street at just the right moment, timing a dash across the rail tracks or maximizing a distraction in order to vanish into thin air.<p>To use this edge, the agent must make a successful Notice roll as an action to spot an opportunity to vanish. When a vehicle, two men carrying a sofa, or some other cover comes between the agent and his pursuer, the agent can make a clean getaway with a successful Stealth roll. Vanishing act may only be used to escape when the agent is on foot.<p>In a Chase situation, the agent may perform a Flee action with a distance of two cards between himself and his pursuer at –4 to the maneuver roll and escapes if successful. The penalty is reduced to –2 at a range of three cards and 0 when there are four cards between the agent and his pursuers.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Secret Files of Section D, page 8","notes":"Secret Files of Section D, page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, St d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cn6zm672txt","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"n6bl0LAYVusDCUTY","name":"Limited Edition Model","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The vessel is a special, one-of-a-kind model, either by design or bey piecemeal. It gains one of these Pilot Edges, usable only by the pilot in this craft. The Trademark Weapon must be the craft of the pilot.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d6, Trademark Weapon Edge, Ace Edge"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_us2p9cunc3","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"p33YbAbAYLc44v2g","name":"Gut Feeling","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Pilot knows their craft inside and out, and as such also is uncannily aware of issues or hazards. Pilot gains +2 Repair rolls.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","notes":"Pilot Edges for Savage Worlds, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Piloting d6, Repair d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_us2p9cunc3","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"qFxzcmTkMoLStBbl","name":"Talisman Craftsman","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This is a magical version of the Gadgeteer Edge. Once per game session, a character with the Talisman Edge can create a magic device and imbue it with arcane energy.</p><p> The device uses any power available to a magician or miracle worker in that setting (though this is still subject to Rank restrictions). It has half the creator’s Power Points. Once these are used up, they do not recharge. The ritual to imbue the object takes d20 minutes. Activating the device requires a Smarts (magic) or Spirit (miracles) roll.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 6","notes":"Horror Companion, page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Spirit d8+, Arcane Background (Magic or Miracles), Knowledge (Occult) d8+, arcane skill d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3bzlxtfggr2","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"rLZ5CHKmjnBmnA1A","name":"Gold Bug","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Treasure Hunters are those people that travel the globe looking for treasure and priceless relics. They can be found in ancient burial grounds to ruined cities. Relic Hunters gain a +2 to Academics Tests when determining the location to ancient treasures.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 79","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 79","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sm d6, Academics d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1zofuj1e709","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"rjzBUDw323C3FhUu","name":"Weapons Encylopedia","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero can recall the vital statistics and important quirks of practically all known commercially available weapons. This includes – but is not limited to – general levels of reliability, material composition, ammunition capacity, caliber, possible outfitted accessories, etc. Characters without this ability will only have such information on weapons they own or use regularly and will need to successfully roll a Smarts based Knowledge Skill check to recall important details. In addition, Weapons Encyclopedia also includes knowledge on acquiring weapons, so characters will have a +5 bonus on any Skill checks needed to locate or buy weapons.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 80","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 80","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Sm d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1zofuj1e709","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"sZGkvFbPScCR3Tw7","name":"Older Than I Look","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character has lived lifetimes, increasing his life experiences so that he adds +2 to most Common Knowledge rolls. In a pinch, he may spend a Benny to gain a temporary d4 in any normal Skill (not including Faith, Focus, Psionics, Spellcasting or Weird Science), for the duration of the scene.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 80","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 80","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Ageless"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1zofuj1e709","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"tC0Wvcw1krVbnmsZ","name":"Long Shot","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some shooters can see a far target as if it were right in front of them. If a shooter does not move in a round or has aimed the previous round, the range of his ranged weapon is now doubled. Targets at long range are treated as if they have +1 armor.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 79","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 79","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"H, Marksman, St d8, Shooting d10"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1zofuj1e709","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"teYbYxmaPLxqLSZv","name":"Master of Disguise","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"There is an art to disguise, and if you are very lucky you can fool everyone. You have become an expert at the art of disguise. This goes beyond the level of a regular disguise, involving elements of performance as well, allowing you to inhabit the disguises you create. A Master of Disguise gets a +2 to Persuasion and Stealth rolls that involve trickery of some kind, including disguises, bluffing and outright lying.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 79","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 79","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Persuasion d6, Stealth d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1zofuj1e709","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"tsbnB08oqznjXOtN","name":"Magic Laundry","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"It doesn’t seem to matter what scrapes this suave hero gets into or what he is wearing, his clothing is always immaculate with minimal effort. This agent can take a crumpled shirt from a saddle bag, give it a shake, and it will look as though it has just been pressed. Had a tussle with some cultists on your way to dinner? No problem. Just give that jacket a wipe down with a handkerchief and it will look as good as new.<p>Agents with Magic Laundry gain +1 to Persuasion and Taunt rolls when appearance is a factor, +1 to Stealth rolls when blending in to a crowd is important and looking dirty or unkempt would make the agent stand out, and +1 to Stealth rolls when using <b>Vanishing Act.</b><p>Magic Laundry also gives +2 to Repair rolls to mend items of clothing. With a Raise, the repair is so good, the item looks like new.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Secret Files of Section D, page 8","notes":"Secret Files of Section D, page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cn6zm672txt","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"vbJAwHxaPBZ2lvhp","name":"Photographic Memory","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero can recall everything you’ve seen, read, or experienced perfectly. If you forget some detail your hero experienced, you may spend a Bennie to have the GM remind you.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 78","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 78","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sm d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1zofuj1e709","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"wDnyDxaJxxLKt61F","name":"Destiny's Child","permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"Your hero is favored by Destiny. She draws and plays an additional Adventure Card each game session.</p><p><b>Source: </b>SWADE Adventure Deck, page ","notes":"SWADE Adventure Deck, page ","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ycpXQddJtpY4skQ0","name":"Guts","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This lady has stared the things that lurk in the dark in the face and learned to control her fear. She ignores two points of Fear penalties for both her Spirit roll and any Fright Table result.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 18","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 18","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Sp d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dygc9en5q1d","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"yfmD2r0KworOzXnp","name":"Sound Mind","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This investigator has learned to cope with the terrors he must face and the dark things that lurk in his world. Increase his Sanity by +2.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 6","notes":"Horror Companion, page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3bzlxtfggr2","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"ylbqMo0ruCuV4jwl","name":"Tower Of Will","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some people know their minds better than others and have trained to keep it that way. A character with this Edge may add +2 to any attempt to resist being mentally controlled by unnatural means, whether by a creature’s Special Ability, magical artifact, or magical spell. The +2 bonus also applies to resisting Tests of Wills.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 6","notes":"Horror Companion, page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3bzlxtfggr2","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"zStAgm2DoI5rEJKs","name":"Super-Amalgamated","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You read a lot and tend to use large words. You live by the philosophy of why use a fifty-cent word, when a two-dollar word will do, and your voracious reading has given you a little knowledge across a broad range of subject. Once per game session, you may spend a bennie to recall a useful fact that relates to the current situation.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Pulp Fantastic, page 79","notes":"Pulp Fantastic, page 79","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"WC, Sm d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"GJDx6zyRouhhfhRq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1zofuj1e709","color":"#000000"}}}
